column37: Produced no fireworks over hurdles after winning his maiden (2m4f, soft) but now goes chasing in new headgear for a yard that won this last year; respected.

column36: Good D'patrick debut; unable to get to grips with a front-runner at Fairyhouse; a player
column37: Solid effort on Downpatrick debut before being unable to get to grips with a runaway front-runner at Fairyhouse; that latter form could be misleading and was a better run than it appears; can be a player.

column4: Thank You To All Our Sponsors & Supporters In 2025 (C & G) (Pro/Am) INH Flat Race
column20: 2/1 Riskaway, 5/2 Porthill, 4/1 Tomthescaffolder, 5/1 Minella Jury, 6/1 Justatan, 25/1 Tinto De Verano, 66/1 Sonny Koufax
column36: Point runner-up has a huge absence to overcome but is in the right hands  so respected
column37: Finished a 4.5l runner-up in a Fairyhouse point on sole start in 2022; was bought for 250,000GBP soon afterwards but has been missing since; dam is half-sister to bumper/2m3f and 2m5f hurdle winner Last Of The Bunch; huge absence to overcome but is in the right hands to do that so respected.

column27: M Laurent Kling & M Alain Dambrines
column36: 7l ahead of Saturday's Cheltenham winner Conman John at Punchestown; looks a big player
column37: Placed on all three point starts in 2024 and both bumper runs this year, with similar efforts at Thurles and Punchestown; was 7l ahead of Saturday's Cheltenham novice winner Conman John on latter occasion; looks a big player on that form.

column37: Well beaten on only completed point start and also on bumper debut when keen; may do better with a hood added but others preferred.

column36: Decent pedigree but a hood and tongue-tie on for debut; best watched
column37: Second foal; half-brother to bumper/2m1f-2m4f hurdle winner Thisistheway; dam bumper/2m4f hurdle winner, half-sister to  smart winner Miss Mitch (2m-2m5f hurdle/chase); decent pedigree but a hood and tongue-tie on for debut; best watched for future reference.

column20: 2/1 Riskaway, 5/2 Porthill, 4/1 Tomthescaffolder, 5/1 Minella Jury, 6/1 Justatan, 25/1 Tinto De Verano, 66/1 Sonny Koufax

column37: Brother to a pair of winners including in a bumper; solid debut effort when beaten 11l on debut at Listowel; winners have come out of that race and this gelding should have improved since too so has to be respected.
